OL,6,F"They also only accept blood from a
OL,7,Fdonor that has been showed by blood
OL,8,Ftesting to be negative for this virus
OL,9,Fso there are enormous expensive
OL,10,Fsafeguards built in.
OL,12,F"But like everything it's not perfect
OL,13,Fand sometimes a little virus does slip
OL,14,Fin and a patient will in fact get
OL,15,Fjaundice," she added.
OL,17,FReacting to this interview with Dr
OL,18,FMayne, Paul described her comments as
OL,19,F"quite disturbing".
